Reasoning: The paper deals with the degrees of freedom (DoF) regions of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) interference channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of reconfigurable antennas, which is a topic in networked and distributed systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper proposes systematic constructions of beamforming and nulling matrices, which is a topic in computer engineering (cs.CE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
